# file open/new bit

Check for a returned file descriptor from upload/open. (open dummy parameter)
First argument is file descriptor, second is debug option.


Check mimetype magic number (first few bytes)

If it's not in odt or html then call file convert. (dummy call)

If it's in odf formats, run xml_to_html functions

 that convert 1000 line sections of it to html (1k lines at a time) with inline? style elements.

If it's already html, then run a tidy_up function on it.

If there's no file parameter argument passed in, create an empty odf document, temp .html document ready to be filled in

Returns a medium sized chunk of html (xhtml 1.0 css2/3, or html5) that is as self contained as possible.